<tool id="SAGA.statistics_grid.15" name="Focal PCA on a Grid" version="1.0.0"><description>This tool uses the difference in cell values of a center cell and its neighbours (as specified by the kernel) as features for a Principal Component Analysis (PCA). This method has been used by Thomas and Herzfeld (2004) to parameterize the topography for a subsequent regionalization of climate variables with the principal components as predictors in a regression model. </description><inputs><param name="GRID" label="Grid" help="Grid" type="text" format="image/tiff, application/x-ogc-envi, application/x-ogc-aaigrid, image/png" /><param name="COMPONENTS" label="Number of Components" help="number of first components in the output; set to zero to get all" type="integer" format="image/tiff, application/x-ogc-envi, application/x-ogc-aaigrid, image/png" /><param name="BASE_OUT" label="Output of Base Topographies" help="Output of Base Topographies" type="boolean" format="image/tiff, application/x-ogc-envi, application/x-ogc-aaigrid, image/png" /><param name="OVERWRITE" label="Overwrite Previous Results" help="Overwrite Previous Results" type="boolean" format="image/tiff, application/x-ogc-envi, application/x-ogc-aaigrid, image/png" /><param name="KERNEL_TYPE" label="Kernel Type" help="Kernel Type" type="text" format="image/tiff, application/x-ogc-envi, application/x-ogc-aaigrid, image/png" /><param name="KERNEL_RADIUS" label="Kernel Radius" help="Kernel radius in cells." type="integer" format="image/tiff, application/x-ogc-envi, application/x-ogc-aaigrid, image/png" /><param name="METHOD" label="Method" help="Method" type="text" format="image/tiff, application/x-ogc-envi, application/x-ogc-aaigrid, image/png" /></inputs><outputs><data name="BASE" label="Base Topographies" /><data name="PCA" label="Principal Components" /><data name="EIGEN" label="Eigen Vectors" /></outputs></tool>